"cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.ST" 

This paper deals with differentially private linear regression, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and privacy-preserving data analysis (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of the Gaussian Johnson-Lindenstrauss Transform (JLT), which is a technique commonly used in data science and dimensionality reduction (cs.DS). The paper also involves statistical analysis and hypothesis testing, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and statistics (cs.ST).
